On Thursday, April 22, 2004, at 02:18PM, Dave C. Bolen <dbolen(-at-)shockwaverider.com> wrote:

>"These high silicone content powders withstand temperatures up to 1000 
>degrees F and offer superior durability when compared to brush and 
>spray-on coatings. Must be applied to clean bare metal."
>
>So far, they really do look just like the day I powder coated them!

This is the one time where you can blame the paint, not the painter. Regular paint used in powdercoating won't do. Don't drop it off without explaining what kind of heat resistance you require. Some shops that do powdercoating aren't setup to spray hi temp paint.

